---
import DocLayout from "../../layouts/DocLayout.astro";
---

<DocLayout title="Public Roadmap" description="The AEGIS Initiative development roadmap — current progress, upcoming milestones, and long-term vision.">
  <h1>Public Roadmap</h1>

  <section>
    <p>
      This roadmap tracks the high-level development arc of the AEGIS ecosystem.
      It is updated quarterly and reflects the current state of all public-facing
      components.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Current Phase: Foundation (Q1 2026)</h2>

    <h3>Governance &amp; Architecture</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>&#10003; AEGIS Constitution v0.1 published</li>
      <li>&#10003; Core governance doctrine established</li>
      <li>&#10003; Architecture Decision Records (ADR) framework in place</li>
      <li>&#10003; Cross-component JSON Schema definitions started</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Public Engagement</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>&#10003; NIST AI Risk Management Framework submission (March 2026)</li>
      <li>&#10003; Org-level GitHub presence established</li>
      <li>&#10003; Public documentation site launch (aegis-docs.com)</li>
      <li>&#10003; AEGIS Initiative website (aegis-initiative.com)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Core Platform</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>&#10003; Governance runtime engine (aegis-core) — v0.1.2 stable, 403 tests</li>
      <li>&#10003; Platform API surface (aegis-platform) — operator dashboard and demo API live</li>
      <li>&#10003; Client SDK (aegis-sdk) — TypeScript and Python packages published</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Next Phase: Harden &amp; Extend (Q2 2026)</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Rust production runtime for aegis-core (v0.2.0)</li>
      <li>Federation protocol implementation (RFC-0016)</li>
      <li>Multi-agent governance patterns</li>
      <li>IEEE peer review outcomes</li>
      <li>aegis-core PyPI publication</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Future Phases</h2>

    <h3>Expand (Q3&ndash;Q4 2026)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Multi-tenant governance support</li>
      <li>Plugin architecture for custom policy engines</li>
      <li>Community governance proposals (RFC process)</li>
      <li>SDK ecosystem expansion</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Scale (2027+)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Enterprise deployment patterns</li>
      <li>Compliance framework integrations (SOC 2, ISO 27001)</li>
      <li>Federated governance across organizational boundaries</li>
      <li>Academic partnerships and research collaborations</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>How to Follow Along</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Watch the <a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-initiative" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">aegis-initiative repository</a> for updates</li>
      <li>Join <a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-initiative/discussions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Discussions</a></li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Want to influence the roadmap? Open an issue or discussion to propose
      priorities. See <a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-initiative/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">CONTRIBUTING.md</a>
      for guidelines.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <p>
      This is the public-facing summary. The detailed internal roadmap with
      architecture milestones and specification timelines is maintained in the
      <a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">aegis governance repository</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</DocLayout>
